Well, the whole premise of the site falls apart if you have it much higher than it is. If the daily probability bumps up to, say, 0.03%, you have a 66.6% chance of a K-Class scenario in any given decade; if it hits 0.1%, that chance is 97.4%.

It only seems low because our intuition is really, really not adapted to this sort of problem. Further reading: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birthday_problem








